quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Most Compassionate
  55,2,taught the Quran
  55,3,created humanity
  55,4,˹and˺ taught them speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon ˹travel˺ with precision
  55,6,The stars and the trees bow down ˹in submission˺
  55,7,"As for the sky, He raised it ˹high˺, and set the balance ˹of justice˺"
  55,8,so that you do not defraud the scales
  55,9,"Weigh with justice, and do not give short measure"
  55,10,He laid out the earth for all beings
  55,11,"In it are fruit, palm trees with date stalks"
  55,12,"and grain with husks, and aromatic plants"
  55,13,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you ˹humans and jinn˺ both deny
  55,14,He created humankind from ˹sounding˺ clay like pottery
  55,15,and created jinn from a ˹smokeless˺ flame of fire
  55,16,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,17,˹He is˺ Lord of the two easts and the two wests
  55,18,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,19,He merges the two bodies of ˹fresh and salt˺ water
  55,20,yet between them is a barrier they never cross
  55,21,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,22,Out of both ˹waters˺ come forth pearls and coral
  55,23,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,24,"To Him belong the ships with raised sails, sailing through the seas like mountains"
  55,25,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,26,Every being on earth is bound to perish
  55,27,"Only your Lord Himself, full of Majesty and Honour, will remain ˹forever˺"
  55,28,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,29,All those in the heavens and the earth are dependent on Him. Day in and day out He has something to bring about
  55,30,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,31,"We will soon attend to you ˹for judgment˺, O two multitudes ˹of jinn and humans˺"
  55,32,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,33,"O assembly of jinn and humans! If you can penetrate beyond the realms of the heavens and the earth, then do so. ˹But˺ you cannot do that without ˹Our˺ authority"
  55,34,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,35,"Flames of fire and ˹molten˺ copper will be sent against you, and you will not be able to defend one another"
  55,36,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,37,"˹How horrible will it be˺ when the heavens will split apart, becoming rose-red like ˹burnt˺ oil"
  55,38,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,39,On that Day there will be no need for any human or jinn to be asked about their sins
  55,40,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,41,"The wicked will be recognized by their appearance, then will be seized by ˹their˺ forelocks and feet"
  55,42,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,43,"˹They will be told,˺ “This is the Hell which the wicked denied.”"
  55,44,They will alternate between its flames and scalding water
  55,45,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,46,And whoever is in awe of standing before their Lord will have two Gardens
  55,47,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,48,˹Both will be˺ with lush branches
  55,49,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,50,In each ˹Garden˺ will be two flowing springs
  55,51,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,52,In each will be two types of every fruit
  55,53,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,54,Those ˹believers˺ will recline on furnishings lined with rich brocade. And the fruit of both Gardens will hang within reach
  55,55,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,56,"In both ˹Gardens˺ will be maidens of modest gaze, who no human or jinn has ever touched before"
  55,57,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,58,Those ˹maidens˺ will be ˹as elegant˺ as rubies and coral
  55,59,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,60,Is there any reward for goodness except goodness
  55,61,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,62,And below these two ˹Gardens˺ will be two others
  55,63,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,64,Both will be dark green
  55,65,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,66,In each will be two gushing springs
  55,67,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,68,"In both will be fruit, palm trees, and pomegranates"
  55,69,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,70,"In all Gardens will be noble, pleasant mates"
  55,71,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,72,"˹They will be˺ maidens with gorgeous eyes, reserved in pavilions"
  55,73,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,74,No human or jinn has ever touched these ˹maidens˺ before
  55,75,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,76,All ˹believers˺ will be reclining on green cushions and splendid carpets
  55,77,Then which of your Lord’s favours will you both deny
  55,78,"Blessed is the Name of your Lord, full of Majesty and Honour"